nt water or something to drink to avoid dehydration. Most resident forget to do this and they end up being ill.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Check if resident is wet or dirty every 2 hours. Clean resident with paper towel or wipes. DO NOT USE FACE TOWEL.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Check on resident who are not mobile or are ill every hour to find out if he/she need something or if condition has regressed or improved.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">All incidents, minor and major must be logged in the residents log book and in caregivers log book.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Do laundry. Fold and deliver to resident. </span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Turn off TV, fans, or lights that are not being used including TV in residents room.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Caregivers will be assigned to a certain part of the facility daily. That care giver will be accountable for the condition of that unit and of the residents in that unit.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Caregivers must be visible in the area at all times to assist all the residents.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Caregivers must sanitized their hands after handling a third resident.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Each caregiver is mandated to take One (1) hour of his/her time to conduct an activity with the residents either in the morning or in the afternoon. Log your name in the activity log book. Caregivers must take turn doing activity with residents.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Check appointment board daily. Afternoon caregiver copy of the residents face sheet and 