giver is mandated to take One (1) hour of his/her time to conduct an activity with the residents either in the morning or in the afternoon. Log your name in the activity log book. Caregivers must take turn doing activity with residents.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Check appointment board daily. Afternoon caregiver copy of the residents face sheet and medicine record, write a reminder to the A.M. caregiver of the appointment, give the documents to the A.M. caregiver for the resident to take to his/her appointment. A.M. caregiver get resident ready for the appointment, makes a sandwich for the resident to take if the resident is leaving early in the morning. If resident is going to a hospital and resident is not cognizant, arrange for a driver to escort the resident. Do not send the resident alone.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Do not leave your area unattended. Get another caregiver to watch your area while away.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Socializing with other employees must be conducted during non-working hours.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Keep socializing (speaking) with residents at a minimum length of time to accomplish other duties.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Speak English during work hours.</span></li>\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">WHEN IN DOUBT, ALWAYS ASK THE SUPERVISOR FOR ANSWER.</span></li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n 	<li>\n<span style="font-weight: 400">Notice: Violations or non-compliance to any of the above will result in reprimand or write up and can lead to termination.</span></li>\n</ol>', 'Resident Caregiving', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '175-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-07-10 23:01:52', '2017-07-10 23:01:52', '', 175, 'http://goodsamalf.com/175-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
