(463, 9, '2017-07-10 23:40:31', '2017-07-10 23:40:31', '<b>JOB TITLE: Facility Manager</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400">Department: </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400">Supervised by: Administrator</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400">Supervises: Housekeeping, Kitchen, Caregiver/MedTech, Maintenance</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>POSITION SUMMARY</b><span style="font-weight: 400">:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400">The main responsibilities would be to conduct pre-residency assessments and screening of potential residents and make recommendations for appropriate level of residency admission in conjunction with the Administrator, Owner Group and other team members. This position will alsobe responsible for providing individualized psychosocial support to residents and their families, via family meetings or support groups and assists through the transition process to a higher level of care. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>The Facility Manager Job Duties and Responsibilities Include:</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Leads the service/care plan process by completing the following: partnering with other team members to develop a service/care plan based on the residents psychosocial and functional needs; validating and ensuring each residents plan of care is being followed by all staff members; maintaining a care conference schedule and coordinating the interdisciplinary care/service plan meetings with family members.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Process all admissions and discharge of residents.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ensures proper record keeping of resident information and staff information</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Reports directly to Administrator, providing verbal and written report/recommendation concerning the operation of facility</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Works with Assisted Living Facility staff to communicate with residents and families before plan of care is changed (when possible) or when there is a change in the residents condition. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Maintains and protects the confidentiality of resident information at all times. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Maintain continuing education training for all facility staff members.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ensures compliance of Federal, State, and local regulations, as well as facility policies regarding assisted living and memory care. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Participates in residents assessments and activity plan</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Practices and directs all safety and loss prevention procedures, adhering to universal precautions and all infection control guidelines. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Must be available some evenings, weekends and holidays to provide support and to assist at Continuing Care events. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Identifies, investigates, and coordinates the resolution of grievances and customer service issues. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>QUALIFICATION:</b></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Minimum High School Graduate</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">One to two years related experience and/or training in long term care/assisted living preferred. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Must have knowledge of geriatric population and the aging process; including the physical, psychological and social needs of the elderly. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Strong written and verbal communication skills in English are required. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Serve Safe Certification (within 30 days of hire). </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">Effectively manage and supervise a diverse employee work group. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">The candidate must be willing to complete a Safe Food Handling and Preparation Class within 30 days of hire. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">The successful candidate should be a strong team player, communicator, and facilitator, as well as a skilled negotiator in team dynamics </span><b>PHYSICAL DEMANDS:</b> <span style="font-weight: 400">\r\n\r\n</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400">The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><span style="font-weight: 400"> While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to stand and walk. The employee frequently is required to use hands to finger, handle, or feel; reach with hands and arms; and talk or hear. The employee is occasionally required to stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl. The employee must regularly lift and/or move up to 50 pounds. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, distance vision, and depth perception. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Administrator ( Assisted Living )', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'administrator-assisted-living', '', '', '2017-07-10 23:40:31', '2017-07-10 23:40:31', '', 0, 'http://goodsamalf.com/?post_type=job&#038;p=463', 0, 'job', '', 0),
